Our client

For our client, a fast-growing ISP and Network Provider based in Utrecht, we are looking for a Senior Data Engineer to strengthen their enthusiastic in-house development team. The organization is making significant investments in its data platform, fully leveraging the Microsoft Azure ecosystem. A future-proof, scalable data architecture is central to their continued growth and innovation.




The Role

As a Senior Data Engineer, you will play a key role in designing, building, and operating a modern data platform that fuels business intelligence and decision-making. This is a hands-on position with real architectural impact: you‚Äôll help shape the data landscape while ensuring reliability, performance, and accessibility. Your deep expertise in Azure and data engineering best practices will be essential to success.




Tasks & responsibilities

Design, build, and maintain scalable data pipelines and ELT/ETL processes using Azure Data Factory, Databricks, and related tools;
Develop and optimize data models, data warehouses, and data lakes to support analytics, reporting, and BI use cases;
Ingest and integrate data from a wide range of sources, including databases, APIs, and external data feeds;
Transform raw data into clean, structured, analytics-ready datasets;
Collaborate closely with data analysts and reporting specialists to ensure high-quality, reliable data for Power BI dashboards;
Implement, monitor, and improve data quality, governance, and validation processes;
Troubleshoot complex data issues and provide technical leadership and guidance within the team.




Your Profile

At least 5 years of hands-on experience in a data engineering role;
Strong, proven experience with Microsoft Azure, including Azure Data Factory, Azure SQL Database, and related Azure data services;
Experience with Azure Databricks for large-scale data processing and transformation;
Solid background in building and maintaining ELT pipelines, data warehouses, and data lakes;
